cs.LO, cs.PL, cs.SE, cs.AI, cs.FL

Reasoning: 
- cs.LO (Logic in Computer Science) is the most likely category as the paper deals with automatic synthesis, which is a logical problem. 
- cs.PL (Programming Languages) is also likely as the paper proposes a user-friendly format for specifying partial implementations. 
- cs.SE (Software Engineering) is another possible category as the paper discusses a method to ease the specification work, which is a common problem in software engineering. 
- cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) is a possible category as the paper deals with state of the art synthesizers, which are often used in AI applications. 
- cs.FL (Formal Languages and Automata Theory) is also a possible category as the paper deals with reactive synthesis problems, which are often studied in the context of formal languages and automata theory.
